---
import LegacyLayout from "../layouts/LegacyLayout.astro";
---

<LegacyLayout title="Summer Lectures" styles={["/css/about.css"]}>
<main>
            <div class="container">
                <h3><i class="material-icons" style="font-size: 1.2em">brightness_low</i> Summer Lectures 2026</h3>

                <p>
                    Although the BCA Math Team is typically geared towards high school students, it has recently begun
                    offering lecture series during the summer to help prepare rising high school freshmen and middle
                    schoolers. This summer, lecture series will be offered in Algebra, Number Theory, Combinatorics, and
                    Geometry throughout August.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Each lecture series will meet four times via Zoom. More details will be posted as they are finalized.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <a
                        class="summer-interest-form"
                        href="https://forms.gle/mpjr3zGfEDffPLYRA"
                        target="_blank"
                        rel="noreferrer">Summer Lectures Interest Form</a
                    >
                </p>
                <p>
                    For questions, contact <a href="mailto:aalpat27@bergen.org">aalpat27@bergen.org</a> or{" "}
                    <a href="mailto:lamto28@bergen.org">lamto28@bergen.org</a>.
                </p>
                <h4>Algebra</h4>
                <p class="summer-course-meta">
                    <strong>Teacher:</strong> Skanda Ramanathan<br />
                    <strong>Google Classroom:</strong>{" "}
                    <a href="https://classroom.google.com/c/ODcwNzIyNzM1NDAw?cjc=smavdwea" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"
                        >Join classroom</a
                    > <span aria-hidden="true">&middot;</span> Code: <code>smavdwea</code>
                </p>
                <p>
                    Students will explore a collection of powerful algebraic techniques frequently used in mathematics
                    competitions. Topics include Vieta's Formulas, methods for finding polynomial roots, arithmetic and
                    geometric sequences and series, and fundamental trigonometry. Along the way, we will learn tools
                    such as the Rational Root Theorem, Descartes' Rule of Signs, and important trigonometric identities,
                    applying them to solve challenging competition-style problems efficiently.
                </p>
                <p><b>Dates:</b> Sundays at 3:00 PM Eastern Time (8/9, 8/16, 8/23, 8/30)</p>

                <h4>Number Theory</h4>
                <p class="summer-course-meta">
                    <strong>Teacher:</strong> Bozhan Shang<br />
                    <strong>Google Classroom:</strong>{" "}
                    <a href="https://classroom.google.com/c/ODcwODk3NTAyMzc3?cjc=5zcqza6r" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"
                        >Join classroom</a
                    > <span aria-hidden="true">&middot;</span> Code: <code>5zcqza6r</code>
                </p>
                <p>
                    Students will explore the fundamentals of the integers. Key topics include modular arithmetic,
                    divisibility, and number bases. We will learn to apply results such as Fermat's Little Theorem,
                    Euler's Theorem, and the Chinese Remainder Theorem in competition math.
                </p>
                <p><b>Dates:</b> Fridays at 6:30 PM Eastern Time (8/7, 8/14, 8/21, 8/28)</p>

                <h4>Combinatorics</h4>
                <p class="summer-course-meta">
                    <strong>Teacher:</strong> Lam To<br />
                    <strong>Google Classroom:</strong>{" "}
                    <a href="https://classroom.google.com/c/ODcwODkxMjkxNTE4?cjc=5ertxiry" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"
                        >Join classroom</a
                    > <span aria-hidden="true">&middot;</span> Code: <code>5ertxiry</code>
                </p>
                <p>
                    Students will strengthen their skills in constructive counting, casework, and expected value through
                    guided problems using higher-level techniques such as bijections and generating functions. Problems
                    will range from late AMC through early- and mid-AIME level, with selected walkthrough problems drawn
                    from the later AIME problem range.
                </p>
                <p><b>Dates:</b> Fridays, 4:00-5:30 PM Eastern Time (8/7, 8/14, 8/21, 8/28)</p>

                <h4>Geometry</h4>
                <p class="summer-course-meta">
                    <strong>Teachers:</strong> Lam To and Aalok Pathak<br />
                    <strong>Google Classroom:</strong>{" "}
                    <a href="https://classroom.google.com/c/ODcwODkxMTYzMTQ3?cjc=cjcnnxdk" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"
                        >Join classroom</a
                    > <span aria-hidden="true">&middot;</span> Code: <code>cjcnnxdk</code>
                </p>
                <p>
                    Students will review key results including Stewart's Theorem, Ptolemy's Theorem, Power of a Point,
                    the Laws of Sines and Cosines, similar-triangle ratios, and area formulas. More involved problems
                    will develop angle chasing, identifying cyclic quadrilaterals, and working with key points of a
                    triangle. The lecture will primarily cover late AMC through early- and mid-AIME problems, with
                    selected walkthrough problems drawn from the later AIME problem range.
                </p>
                <p><b>Dates:</b> Tuesdays, 4:00-5:30 PM Eastern Time (8/4, 8/11, 8/18, 8/25)</p>
            </div>
        </main>
</LegacyLayout>

<style>
    .summer-interest-form {
        font-weight: 600;
        text-decoration: underline;
        text-underline-offset: 0.18em;
    }

    .summer-course-meta {
        margin-top: -0.5rem;
        padding-left: 0.9rem;
        border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0;
        color: #555;
        font-size: 0.95rem;
        line-height: 1.75;
    }

    .summer-course-meta code {
        padding: 0.08rem 0.3rem;
        background: #f2f2f2;
        border-radius: 2px;
        color: #333;
        font-family: monospace;
    }
</style>
